<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<HTML lang="en">
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Add MailHost</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H2>Add MailHost</H2>

<dtml-var "HelpSys.HelpButton('Mail-Host_Add.dtml', 'MailHost')">

<P>
A Mail Host allows Zope to send email.
</P>

<P>
Use the form below to specify the options for your Mail Host.
<EM>Local Host</EM> is the name of the machine Zope is running on.
<EM>SMTP Host</EM> is the name of the mail server machine.
<EM>SMTP Port</EM> is the port on which the mail server is running
the SMTP service.
<EM>Max. Timeout</EM> is how long Zope should wait before giving up
when trying to send mail.
</P>

<FORM ACTION="manage_addMailHost" METHOD="POST">
<TABLE CELLSPACING="2">
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
  <TH ALIGN="LEFT">Id</TH>
  <TD ALIGN="LEFT">
    <INPUT TYPE="TEXT" NAME="id" SIZE="40" value="MailHost">
  </TD>
</TR>
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
  <TH ALIGN="LEFT"><EM>Title</EM></TH>
  <TD ALIGN="LEFT">
    <INPUT TYPE="TEXT" NAME="title" SIZE="40">
  </TD>
</TR>
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
  <TH ALIGN="LEFT">SMTP Host</TH>
  <TD ALIGN="LEFT">
    <INPUT TYPE="TEXT" NAME="smtp_host" SIZE="40">
  </TD>
</TR>
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
  <TH ALIGN="LEFT">SMTP Port</TH>
  <TD ALIGN="LEFT">
    <INPUT TYPE="TEXT" NAME="smtp_port:int" SIZE="4" VALUE="25">
  </TD>
</TR>
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD><BR><INPUT TYPE="SUBMIT" VALUE=" Add "></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</FORM>

</BODY>
</HTML>
